# Project Structure

## QML Lab (Python)

```
src/
├── classical/     # Classical models — Perceptron, TransformerMini, RNNMini
├── quantum/       # QNN, HybridModel, AmplitudeEncoding
├── data/          # generators, augmentation, poisoning
└── training/      # trainer, metrics, curriculum

experiments/
└── exp_NNN_<name>/
    ├── hypothesis.md   ← required BEFORE run.py
    ├── run.py
    └── results.md      ← filled AFTER running

logs/
└── experiments.jsonl   ← append-only, never delete

dashboard/
└── app.py              ← Streamlit
```

## Node/TypeScript Backend (when scaffolded)

```
src/
├── @types/
├── config/         env.ts, container.ts
├── domain/         entities, repository interfaces, domain events, value objects
├── application/    use cases, DTOs
├── infrastructure/ database, cache, queue, http, outbox, logging
├── presentation/   http routes + schemas, health endpoints
└── shared/         Result, AppError, EventBus, pagination, utils
```

## Naming Conventions

| Artifact | Pattern |
|---|---|
| Python modules | `snake_case.py` |
| TypeScript files | `kebab-case.ts` |
| TS Classes/Types | `PascalCase` |
| TS functions/vars | `camelCase` |
| Constants | `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` |
| Experiment folders | `exp_NNN_descriptive_name` |
| Git branches | `feat/`, `fix/`, `exp/` prefixes |

## File Creation Rules

- Never create logic files outside the canonical structure above
- Never create a `run.py` without a sibling `hypothesis.md`
- Never create a `results.md` before running the experiment
- Config values belong in `config/` or `config/experiments.yaml` — never hardcoded
